## 3. Create a Webhook in Qovery

To create a webhook in Qovery, have a look at [this section][docs.using-qovery.integration.webhook#creating-a-webhook]. For the URL, use the Slack Webhook URL that you got from the previous step. 

### Considerations

- You can have multiple webhooks targeting different Slack channels.
- You can specify the events that you want to receive. E.g. if you just want to be notified when a deployment failed, then use `"events": ["DEPLOYMENT_FAILURE"]`. All the events and the description are available [on our Webhook section][docs.using-qovery.integration.webhook].
- You can turn off or delete your webhooks at any time from the webhook section.

Check out [this page][docs.using-qovery.integration.webhook] for further details on how to use and configure the WebHook.

